 smuggling routes, arms and military hardware in Syria and Iraq. The group attracted significant numbers of foreign extremists to live and fight in its &#x201C;caliphate.&#x201D;"}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"ISIS leader Abu Bakr al Baghdadi, who sent the first ISIS terrorist attackers to Europe in 2014, has not yet been captured. But with the loss of almost all the territory it controlled, ISIS propaganda has decreased considerably as has the flow of foreign jihadists into Syria and Iraq."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Our Middle East intelligence and policy experts will be on the hook to assess whether ISIS&#x2019;s ability to recruit followers will be significantly eroded with the loss of its geographic space even if ISIS is transformed into a &#x201C;virtual caliphate.&#x201D;"}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"American forces will also need to plan for targeting the remaining estimated 20,000 to 30,000 ISIS fighters in the Iraq-Syria battlespace."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Emphasizing that &#x201C;when the U.S. retreats, chaos follows,&#x201D; Pompeo used his Cairo speech to highlight lessons learned from the Obama administration&#x2019;s precipitous withdrawal of U.S. forces from Iraq. That withdrawal helped create the conditions for the massive growth and spread of ISIS in the region."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"After removing U.S. combat troops from Iraq in 2011, President Obama was forced to send them back in 2014 to fight ISIS. The U.S. currently has about 5,200 troops in Iraq, where ISIS stages occasional attacks. President Trump said in December he has no plans to reduce U.S. troop strength there."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Iranian proxies in Iraq are trying to induce the withdrawal of U.S. troops from that nation to strengthen Iran&#x2019;s effort to secure pre-eminent influence in Iraq."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"In his Cairo speech, Pompeo declared the U.S. would be a faithful ally, but one that would ask our regional partners to take primary responsibility for their own security."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"The U.S. is protected by two great oceans and enjoys good relations with our neighbors to the south and north. Over the years, many Americans have strongly desired to avoid becoming entangled in world affairs &#x2013; especially where U.S. troops could be called into battle."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"But the world is more interconnected today, including through cyberspace, than at any time in history. Our enemies can reach us in spite of our geographic separation from other parts of the world provided by the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"U.S. efforts at nation-building in other countries have been extraordinarily costly to us &#x2013; both in the billions of dollars we have spent and more importantly in lost American lives."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Still, despite all the sacrifices of Americans and deaths of members of the U.S. military and civilians, we have been unable to prevent the growth of disaffected people in failed states who are vulnerable to extremists&#x2019; exploitation."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Al Qaeda is still a threat. Its leader &#x2013; Ayman al-Zawahiri &#x2013; is still committed to his declaration of jihad against the U.S."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Even if the local authorities are unable to eliminate the underlying causes of terrorism we must be careful about outsourcing our national security."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"The late Charles Krauthammer articulated a strategy of &#x201C;forward defense&#x201D; where we confront our enemies &#x201C;over there&#x201D; rather than allow them to plan and execute attacks on our homeland from ungoverned space in failed states. Krauthammer believed we should only risk spilling American blood and treasure when there was &#x201C;strategic necessity.&#x201D;"}},{"is":"paragraph","pro